Hi @Luap99,

Yes, I can confirm that `ping` works just fine and I think it always has:

```
127.0.0.1   localhost localhost.localdomain localhost4 localhost4.localdomain4
::1         localhost localhost.localdomain localhost6 localhost6.localdomain6
# used by slirp4netns
10.0.2.100	8f03d93b6012 test
10.0.2.2 host.containers.internal
[root@8f03d93b6012 /]# ping `hostname`
PING 8f03d93b6012 (10.0.2.100) 56(84) bytes of data.
64 bytes from 8f03d93b6012 (10.0.2.100): icmp_seq=1 ttl=64 time=0.028 ms
64 bytes from 8f03d93b6012 (10.0.2.100): icmp_seq=2 ttl=64 time=0.030 ms
64 bytes from 8f03d93b6012 (10.0.2.100): icmp_seq=3 ttl=64 time=0.030 ms
```

In the meantime, I could also find out some more about the Java tool and what it is using to resolve the address.
It's issuing a call to [`InetAddress.getAllByName()`](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/net/InetAddress.html#getAllByName(java.lang.String)) to get all the addresses from the host.
I did a quick test run with the following little snippet:

```java
package com.gvenzl;

import java.net.InetAddress;

public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args)throws Exception {
        InetAddress localhost = InetAddress.getLocalHost();
        String hostname = localhost.getHostName();
        System.out.println("Hostname: " + hostname);
        InetAddress address = InetAddress.getByName(hostname);
        System.out.println("Local address: " + address.getHostAddress());
        InetAddress[] addresses = InetAddress.getAllByName(hostname);
        for (InetAddress addr : addresses) {
            System.out.println("Address: " + addr.getHostAddress());
            System.out.println("Hostname: " + addr.getHostName());
            System.out.println("Is loopback addr: " + addr.isLoopbackAddress());
        }
    }
}
```

but that also seems to return the correct results and, more importantly, resolves the hostname from `/etc/hosts`:

```
[root@8f03d93b6012 /]# java Main
Hostname: 8f03d93b6012
Local address: 10.0.2.100
Address: 10.0.2.100
Hostname: 8f03d93b6012
Is loopback addr: false
```

I will keep looking but for now, thank you both very much for your help on this!
If I get to the bottom of this, I will update this issue so that perhaps the analysis is of help for future readers of this issue.
